<TITLE> Bhuiyan backers set to hold meeting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 15 (bdnews24.com) -- BNP "reformists" are set to hold a meeting Saturday afternoon. The BNP leaders, led by Abdul Mannan Bhuiyan, are expected to come up with a crucial announcement after the meeting in Gulshan, several senior leaders told bdnews24.com. Mofiqul Hasan Tripti, a backer of Bhuiyan, has said that as many as 130 leaders are with the group. The meeting comes amid a broader divide in the BNP, which was laid open after party chairperson Khaleda Zia was arrested on Sept 3. The crisis deepened in the troubled BNP after Khaleda expelled Bhuiyan from the pary and installed Khandaker Delwar Hossain as secetary general. bd
